WEBVTT

00:17.612 --> 00:19.182
- Nobody's reported them
missing.

00:19.248 --> 00:20.752
Nobody's called
in a disturbance.

00:20.819 --> 00:23.190
These houses are an acre apart.

00:23.257 --> 00:24.726
Brenda's neighbors
were 10 feet away

00:24.793 --> 00:27.499
and all they heard over the
Orioles was pounding on a wall.

00:27.566 --> 00:28.534
- Right.

00:30.539 --> 00:32.742
There it is. Bishop Low's.

00:35.447 --> 00:36.750
Porch light's off.

00:39.289 --> 00:41.125
I'll be at the front door.

01:01.600 --> 01:03.972
Police!

01:05.374 --> 01:06.777
Bill.

01:39.777 --> 01:41.278
Police!

02:34.485 --> 02:37.792
Hey!

02:41.767 --> 02:43.036
- Charming.

02:43.103 --> 02:44.238
- Sorry.

03:11.660 --> 03:13.130
It's all clear.

03:15.167 --> 03:18.340
Judging by the jewelry
I saw dumped in the toilet,

03:18.406 --> 03:19.576
wouldn't peg this a robbery.

03:19.643 --> 03:22.047
- No. Checkbook's right there.

03:22.114 --> 03:23.249
Kidnapping?

03:23.316 --> 03:24.519
- God, I hope that
they got outta here

03:24.586 --> 03:26.523
before anything like
that could happen,

03:26.590 --> 03:28.794
and somewhere
we can find them first.

03:39.348 --> 03:41.018
Okay. Thanks, Fred.

03:41.085 --> 03:44.158
Well, at least half
of Sam's list is still alive.

03:44.224 --> 03:46.262
Our boys just found
the Laffertys' stake president,

03:46.329 --> 03:48.266
Mr. Stowe,
and his wife asleep in bed.

03:49.569 --> 03:51.339
Say they haven't seen
anything unusual.

03:51.405 --> 03:54.011
No bearded men.

03:54.077 --> 03:56.917
But also said they haven't
heard from the Lows for a week.

03:58.821 --> 03:59.656
Which is unusual.

03:59.722 --> 04:01.526
- L--hey, Morris.
- Sir.

04:01.593 --> 04:03.329
- First light, I need you to...

04:03.396 --> 04:04.700
Track the last knowns
of the Lows.

04:04.767 --> 04:06.102
- Yes, sir.
Where would you--

04:06.169 --> 04:07.237
where would you like me
to look?

04:09.308 --> 04:10.210
- Talk to neighbors.

04:10.277 --> 04:12.916
- Neighbors.

04:12.983 --> 04:14.451
- The Lows' kids.

04:14.519 --> 04:16.857
Kids.
- Um...

04:16.924 --> 04:20.163
You know, phone records
and credit cards,

04:20.230 --> 04:22.434
that kind of thing.

04:22.502 --> 04:25.406
Careful. Go.

04:29.649 --> 04:31.686
You and me, we need
to keep pushing Robin.

04:31.753 --> 04:33.891
If he had these names
up his sleeve...

04:33.957 --> 04:35.795
- That's fine with me.

04:35.862 --> 04:37.131
Yeah.

04:40.839 --> 04:43.209
Sorry, it's a letter
from Dianna asking for help

04:43.276 --> 04:45.114
with, uh,
the Lafferty brothers'

04:45.180 --> 04:47.518
questionable behavior.

04:47.585 --> 04:48.688
- To the president
of your church?

04:48.755 --> 04:50.157
To the living Prophet.

04:50.224 --> 04:52.094
It's kind of like
writing a letter

04:52.160 --> 04:55.000
to Heavenly Father himself.

04:55.067 --> 04:56.736
And it's--it's hard to imagine

04:56.803 --> 05:01.078
an LDS wife doing this
to her own family.

05:03.216 --> 05:05.053
It's extreme.

05:05.119 --> 05:06.155
And this could have--

05:14.506 --> 05:18.413
Oh, gosh.
Bill, we have to find her.

05:20.952 --> 05:23.056
Whoa, you guys are pros.

05:23.122 --> 05:25.528
- They look great.
- Yeah.

05:25.594 --> 05:28.333
- Hey, Jeb, I called, um,
Nana and Papa

05:28.400 --> 05:29.836
and, uh, told them to hold off

05:29.903 --> 05:31.472
on coming
for the girls' baptisms.

05:31.540 --> 05:33.578
They're a little anxious
to know when we, um,

05:33.644 --> 05:35.347
might be moving the date to.

05:35.414 --> 05:37.417
- Girls do not need baptizing.

05:37.484 --> 05:39.488
I mean, look at them,
clean as whistles.

05:41.493 --> 05:44.064
That's a bath, not a baptism.
- Bath, bath.

05:44.131 --> 05:45.568
You're thinking of a bath.

05:45.635 --> 05:47.471
- You know who should give
a God damn about baptism?

05:47.539 --> 05:49.041
Hey, Mom. That's a no-no.

05:52.982 --> 05:54.352
Annie drew the rainbow.

05:55.621 --> 05:56.790
You guys did this?

05:56.857 --> 05:59.896
It's great.
- See this? Beautiful.

05:59.963 --> 06:01.265
Murder of the
young mother and daughter,

06:01.332 --> 06:04.237
detectives are investigating
ties to Satanists

06:04.304 --> 06:05.574
and other fringe sects known

06:05.641 --> 06:07.044
to practice
ritualized killing.

06:10.450 --> 06:12.487
- Skates off
and shoes on in 20.

06:13.991 --> 06:14.793
Honey--

06:14.860 --> 06:15.995
Hmm?
- Is that true?

06:16.061 --> 06:17.565
The Jews, they need baptisms.

06:17.632 --> 06:18.701
Hello? Are you still there?

06:18.768 --> 06:21.005
Yes, uh,
this is Detective Pyre.

06:21.071 --> 06:22.274
So sorry, Brother Pyre,

06:22.341 --> 06:24.579
I hope your hair hasn't
gone gray from waiting.

06:24.646 --> 06:26.148
- No, it's fine.

06:26.215 --> 06:27.852
I got ahold
of the original letter

06:27.919 --> 06:29.790
that Sister Lafferty
mailed to the Prophet.

06:29.856 --> 06:31.125
- Mm-hmm.

06:31.192 --> 06:32.728
I see here
he directed the matter

06:32.795 --> 06:36.469
to Bishop Low and to a member
of the bishopric,

06:36.536 --> 06:38.273
LeConte Bascom.

06:38.340 --> 06:39.474
- Can you--

06:39.542 --> 06:42.414
B-A-S-C-O-M.

06:44.051 --> 06:45.588
- Wonderful--you've been
a great help, Brother.

06:45.655 --> 06:47.592
Thank you so much.

06:47.658 --> 06:48.927
You call back any time.

06:48.994 --> 06:52.100
The Prophet's praying
for your investigation.

06:52.167 --> 06:53.135
- He is?

06:57.343 --> 06:58.614
That's all we're gonna need.

06:58.681 --> 07:00.083
I appreciate that
very much, Brother.

07:00.150 --> 07:02.053
Thanks. Bye.

07:04.358 --> 07:05.394
Everything okay?

07:05.460 --> 07:07.566
Yeah.
Everything's great, Mom.

07:07.632 --> 07:09.235
That radio reporter knows

07:09.302 --> 07:11.507
as much about this case

07:11.573 --> 07:15.581
as our toaster, okay?

07:15.648 --> 07:17.384
Should we unplug
our toaster too?

07:18.988 --> 07:22.394
You know, if the Jews
don't accept Christ,

07:22.460 --> 07:25.066
they--they're gonna
find themselves

07:25.133 --> 07:28.540
in the Telestial Kingdom
with Hitler.

07:28.607 --> 07:31.279
- Josie, that kind of talk
scares the girls.

07:31.345 --> 07:32.649
Remember we talked about that?
- Mom, Mom--

07:32.715 --> 07:33.917
Don't speak back to me,

07:33.984 --> 07:35.821
because I don't speak
like that with the girls.

07:35.888 --> 07:37.424
- You want to go for a walk?
Yes.

07:37.492 --> 07:38.794
Yeah?

07:38.861 --> 07:39.796
- Yes.
- Let's go for a walk.

07:39.863 --> 07:41.231
I'm sorry.

07:41.298 --> 07:42.735
She's sorry, Beccs.

07:42.802 --> 07:44.171
Sorry.

07:44.238 --> 07:45.742
- I'm gonna meet you
in the hallway, all right?

07:45.808 --> 07:47.144
- Okay.
- Be right back.

07:47.210 --> 07:48.379
- Okay.
- All right.

07:48.446 --> 07:49.615
- Okay.

07:51.887 --> 07:53.122
- I know she doesn't mean it.

07:53.189 --> 07:57.164
It's just the things she says
around the girls,

07:57.231 --> 07:59.903
and I--

07:59.969 --> 08:02.975
I can't calm her down
like you can.

08:03.042 --> 08:05.314
And you're not always here,
and so...

08:08.920 --> 08:13.429
Can we--can we please
try the medications?

08:20.912 --> 08:24.017
- Call her doctor and ask
about side effects, okay?

08:28.861 --> 08:30.898
- Brother Pyre.
- Good morning.

08:32.868 --> 08:34.204
Uh, LeConte Bascom.
- Brother Bascom.

08:34.271 --> 08:35.741
Ignore the creases in my tie.

08:35.808 --> 08:37.310
Had to shake a leg
to meet you before we opened.

08:37.377 --> 08:39.147
- Oh, I appreciate the haste,
Brother, thank you.

08:39.214 --> 08:40.584
- Oh, it's nothing.

08:40.651 --> 08:43.991
The, uh, Prophet's office urged
me to help you any way I can.

08:44.057 --> 08:45.894
Take one. They're cinnamon.
Oh, gosh.

08:45.961 --> 08:47.832
I can't keep
disappointing my dentist.

08:47.899 --> 08:49.969
I can't do it.
Thank you, though.

08:50.036 --> 08:51.506
But I was hoping
you could shed some light--

08:51.573 --> 08:53.042
- Yes, yes,
about Dianna's letter.

08:53.109 --> 08:55.179
The Prophet's office
filled me in.

08:56.650 --> 08:59.488
- Oh, good. Good.

08:59.555 --> 09:01.560
Okay.

09:01.627 --> 09:03.229
So let's start
with what you did

09:03.295 --> 09:05.166
when you first received
the letter.

09:05.233 --> 09:07.470
Well, I had a word with Ron

09:07.538 --> 09:09.742
when he came in looking
to get approved on a loan.

09:09.809 --> 09:11.713
Duplex sales
are in the dang gutter

09:11.779 --> 09:14.318
because interest rates
are what they are, and--

09:14.384 --> 09:17.390
and you are overleveraged.
I just wish it were less risky.

09:17.457 --> 09:18.694
- "Risky"?

09:18.761 --> 09:20.229
You've never used that word
with me before.

09:20.296 --> 09:22.601
This is lean, it is a four-plex
with a heavily-vetted client.

09:22.668 --> 09:24.573
You know my word is oak.
You know that.

09:24.639 --> 09:25.842
- If it were up to me alone,

09:25.908 --> 09:29.114
I'd give you
the dang bank vault, Brother.

09:29.181 --> 09:31.018
- Who else is it up to?
Maybe I should speak to them.

09:31.085 --> 09:33.657
Ron, it's my file. I'm sorry.

09:35.092 --> 09:38.032
- Brother Bascom,
I don't get this loan,

09:38.099 --> 09:40.370
then I can't afford
to keep operating.

09:40.436 --> 09:42.441
And I'm gonna lose my business
and I'm gonna lose my home.

09:42.508 --> 09:45.915
What, my wife is next?

09:45.981 --> 09:49.121
Do you want me
to lose my children, hmm?

09:49.188 --> 09:50.156
- Ron...

09:52.762 --> 09:54.297
The church has received
a letter

09:54.364 --> 09:57.738
asking for intervention in your
brothers' anti-tax organizing.

09:59.676 --> 10:02.682
The church passed it on to me.

10:02.748 --> 10:05.487
- So you won't sell me
because Dan refuses

10:05.554 --> 10:06.957
to pay sales tax in a store?

10:07.024 --> 10:08.594
It's because
of his failure to pay tax

10:08.660 --> 10:10.330
on your father's home

10:10.396 --> 10:13.904
as part of a scheme to
challenge taxation as a whole.

10:13.970 --> 10:15.608
Filing a lawsuit to say
the 16th Amendment

10:15.674 --> 10:17.645
hasn't been ratified?

10:17.712 --> 10:18.914
That's kicking up dust.

10:18.980 --> 10:21.620
- Okay, and what's he got
to do with me?

10:21.687 --> 10:25.026
- Ron, your wife
wrote the letter.

10:25.093 --> 10:27.431
She seems pretty worried
about it.

10:31.472 --> 10:34.713
Now don't you lay the blame
at her feet, all right?

10:34.779 --> 10:36.983
Those ERA types
spawn more varieties

10:37.050 --> 10:38.720
of bad influence
than we can stamp out.

10:38.787 --> 10:40.356
You know, Phil Donahue's

10:40.423 --> 10:42.361
positively urging our wives
to run wild.

10:42.427 --> 10:45.399
I'm sure it was
only out of concern

10:45.466 --> 10:47.672
for the man that she loves--
that's you--

10:47.738 --> 10:50.110
but anti-government schemes

10:50.176 --> 10:52.848
leaves me in no position
to walk out on a limb with you.

10:52.915 --> 10:54.418
- Look at my hands.
I'm a builder.

10:54.485 --> 10:56.288
What use would I have
for anti-government schemes?

10:56.355 --> 10:57.691
I don't make it my business

10:57.758 --> 10:58.961
to understand
that sort of thing,

10:59.028 --> 11:00.564
but your brother's been
very outspoken

11:00.631 --> 11:02.902
about his new
political hobbies,

11:02.968 --> 11:05.072
and, well, he--

11:05.139 --> 11:09.414
he portrays it
as a family affair, Ron.

11:09.481 --> 11:12.153
Thank you for your time.

11:12.220 --> 11:15.059
Was Ron angry with Dianna?

11:15.126 --> 11:17.264
- Oh, heck. No, no, no.

11:17.330 --> 11:19.669
No, it was Dan that was making
a mess of their name,

11:19.736 --> 11:22.107
not his sweet wife.

11:22.174 --> 11:25.346
No, Dan was threatening
the reputation of the church,

11:25.413 --> 11:28.385
and as a result,
Ron's own livelihood.

11:29.755 --> 11:31.660
- So Ron was only
angry with Dan?

11:31.727 --> 11:32.695
Wouldn't you be?

11:32.761 --> 11:34.131
It'd take hours to drive you

11:34.198 --> 11:36.770
around all the homes that
Ron has put up around here.

11:36.836 --> 11:39.475
Dan...

11:39.542 --> 11:41.245
Dan's a wrecking ball.

11:56.008 --> 11:59.916
Brenda just couldn't
let a thing alone.

11:59.982 --> 12:01.653
- You think Brenda
helped write that?

12:01.720 --> 12:03.055
If Dianna wrote this letter,

12:03.122 --> 12:05.761
then you can be sure that
Brenda put the pen in her hand.

12:07.264 --> 12:08.601
Did Dan know about this letter?

12:08.667 --> 12:11.105
He wouldn't have paid it
much mind if he did.

12:11.171 --> 12:14.745
He knows more than any
of the wives about her faith.

12:14.812 --> 12:16.382
And at the time that
this letter was written,

12:16.449 --> 12:21.760
his message was bigger
than the 4th of July.

12:29.742 --> 12:31.980
Don't let the government
steal any more money

12:32.047 --> 12:33.517
out of your pockets.

12:33.583 --> 12:35.353
You keep what's yours.

12:37.423 --> 12:41.332
Where'd the founding fathers
say you needed

12:41.399 --> 12:43.937
a Social Security number
to be an American?

12:46.776 --> 12:50.183
They tag us like cattle,
track us down,

12:50.249 --> 12:53.122
and then claim half
of what's ours is theirs.

12:53.189 --> 12:57.197
No! They don't own me,
and they don't own you, either.

12:57.264 --> 13:00.571
So vote Lafferty

13:00.638 --> 13:02.842
and live free under the true,

13:02.908 --> 13:06.114
original laws
of the U.S. Constitution.

13:10.657 --> 13:11.926
I suppose
enough people tell you

13:11.993 --> 13:14.097
you're the Kennedys of Utah,

13:14.164 --> 13:17.972
you think it's your destiny
to be in charge.

13:18.039 --> 13:21.847
- You ever heard of
Governor Boggs from Missouri?

13:21.913 --> 13:23.584
He was shot in the head
one night...

13:24.686 --> 13:26.355
Then he pinned

13:26.422 --> 13:30.831
the assassination attempt
on us.

13:30.897 --> 13:32.768
So what did our Prophet do?

13:32.835 --> 13:35.139
He launched
a presidential campaign.

13:35.206 --> 13:36.375
- Well, correct me
if I'm wrong,

13:36.442 --> 13:38.814
but Joe Smith
didn't become president.

13:38.881 --> 13:40.817
- He could have.
He was very popular.

13:40.884 --> 13:42.320
- Like your brother Dan?

13:44.324 --> 13:47.030
- My brother Dan
has always been very popular.

13:47.097 --> 13:48.733
And the only person

13:48.800 --> 13:53.075
who had a problem with Dan
running was our father.

13:53.142 --> 13:54.512
Yeah, she's a gypsy. Huh?

13:54.579 --> 13:55.948
Whoa.

13:56.014 --> 13:57.885
Yeah, she's got me
under her spell.

13:57.952 --> 13:59.421
Whoa, wait. Hold on.

13:59.488 --> 14:00.924
What--what are you
making me do?

14:00.991 --> 14:03.295
Oh, she's making--
what is she making me do?

14:03.362 --> 14:05.400
I'ma--oh--mm.

14:05.467 --> 14:07.905
Oh, no!
She's got me under her spell.

14:07.972 --> 14:10.577
Lord, she's bending me
to her will!

14:10.644 --> 14:12.982
- Dan. All right.

14:13.049 --> 14:14.952
Hey. Hey, Dan.
- Conspirer!

14:19.227 --> 14:23.469
Get hence, serpent. Get!

14:23.537 --> 14:25.508
Get!

14:25.574 --> 14:27.811
Get! Get! All of you!

14:27.878 --> 14:29.347
Go! Get!

14:33.089 --> 14:36.763
Are you wiser
than the Word of Wisdom?

14:36.830 --> 14:41.304
Ungrateful to a wife who
stooped to marry a deadbeat?

14:42.975 --> 14:44.344
I intend to tell Matilda
about this,

14:44.411 --> 14:46.516
and we know
she does not fear divorce.

14:49.187 --> 14:52.226
- The Lord guides
my political vision.

14:52.293 --> 14:54.498
- Wrong!

14:54.565 --> 14:57.671
The voice you hear
is the devil's.

14:57.738 --> 15:02.013
Oh, he--he answers prayers too.

15:05.119 --> 15:08.158
In your cheering crowds,

15:08.225 --> 15:11.933
do you judge what is holy
on what is fashionable?

15:14.772 --> 15:16.108
Yeah. Oh, no.

15:16.175 --> 15:17.945
Your mother and I, we...

15:20.316 --> 15:22.521
We cannot return
to our mission.

15:22.588 --> 15:25.426
All those souls in Louisiana
in need of baptism,

15:25.494 --> 15:29.134
and we must stay here
to save our--our son now.

15:32.741 --> 15:36.983
Flee from temptation, Daniel.
Look away from man's laws.

15:37.050 --> 15:39.989
They're so...

15:40.056 --> 15:43.630
small and temporary.

15:49.074 --> 15:53.650
Lean back toward
Heavenly Father's designs.

15:53.717 --> 15:56.756
Study them closely.

15:57.858 --> 16:00.196
His Word.

16:00.262 --> 16:02.668
Understanding His laws...

16:05.907 --> 16:08.378
Is bliss.

16:13.188 --> 16:15.226
Be my good boy again.

16:20.904 --> 16:22.608
Pray with us.

16:27.316 --> 16:28.720
Our Father in heaven.

16:32.461 --> 16:36.068
May I find the strength...

16:36.135 --> 16:37.604
Guide me...

16:37.671 --> 16:39.708
How deep into study
did Dan go?

16:41.412 --> 16:44.217
Dan just took
our father's words to heart.

16:46.722 --> 16:50.062
Started spending his days
in the BYU library,

16:50.129 --> 16:53.704
researching the early prophets,
and...

16:53.770 --> 16:55.708
he grew frustrated
with the fact that

16:55.774 --> 16:58.078
so much of our history

16:58.145 --> 17:01.117
seemed to have been
purposefully removed

17:01.184 --> 17:05.359
from every library in Utah,
including BYU's.

17:05.426 --> 17:08.600
So Dan started
seeking out saints

17:08.666 --> 17:13.108
who were living
by our original texts.

17:13.175 --> 17:16.081
And then that gave Dan
an excuse

17:16.148 --> 17:18.753
to drive us down
to Colorado City.

17:18.820 --> 17:20.422
We're not supposed
to have anything to do

17:20.489 --> 17:23.563
with these people, Dan.
Turn the truck around.

17:23.630 --> 17:24.665
Dan!

17:24.732 --> 17:27.136
- They study our scriptures,
don't they?

17:27.203 --> 17:29.842
Live His commandments
better than we do.

17:29.909 --> 17:31.546
- This isn't right, Dan.

17:31.613 --> 17:32.748
This isn't--

17:35.521 --> 17:36.823
I don't know about this, Dan.

17:36.890 --> 17:39.127
- And that's what we are here
to address, Robin,

17:39.193 --> 17:40.396
our lack of knowledge.

17:44.839 --> 17:46.408
Quiet here, huh?

17:54.090 --> 17:57.129
There's a lotta houses in need
of that finishing touch, eh?

17:59.134 --> 18:01.372
It's a joke. I'm joking.

18:01.438 --> 18:04.177
Can't charge property tax
on a building

18:04.243 --> 18:06.682
that ain't finished, right?

18:06.749 --> 18:08.485
Yeah.
You guys got it figured out.

18:09.888 --> 18:13.362
Yeah, up north,
they charge property tax

18:13.428 --> 18:16.001
on a home that my dad
owns outright.

18:16.067 --> 18:18.072
Yeah, it's like the government
who actually owns it.

18:18.138 --> 18:19.542
It's highway robbery.

18:19.609 --> 18:21.445
You finish up here.

18:21.513 --> 18:23.883
Let these men get on
their way, Brother Nichols.

18:42.688 --> 18:44.324
- You guys practice
polygamy here?

18:44.391 --> 18:45.593
Dan.

18:45.660 --> 18:47.197
- No, well,
I've been reading about it--

18:47.263 --> 18:50.169
