36:14.389 --> 36:16.728
- Thus sayeth the Lord...

36:18.799 --> 36:22.706
"I command mine handmaid
Emma Smith

36:22.773 --> 36:26.347
"to abide and cleave
unto my servant, Joseph,

36:26.414 --> 36:29.286
"and to none else.

36:29.352 --> 36:33.161
But if she will not abide
this commandment..."

36:39.874 --> 36:42.412
"She shall be destroyed."

36:42.479 --> 36:45.619
- The Heavenly Father
will destroy me?

36:45.686 --> 36:47.523
Me?

36:50.027 --> 36:52.398
Are you certain, Prophet?

37:00.115 --> 37:02.587
I did what the church
taught us to do--

37:02.654 --> 37:05.793
put my questions on the shelf.

37:07.195 --> 37:10.970
It's hard to keep them
up there,

37:11.036 --> 37:13.240
isn't it?

37:19.019 --> 37:20.723
- Did Dan keep his questions
on the shelf?

37:20.790 --> 37:24.831
- If the men I saw
were from Colorado City,

37:24.898 --> 37:26.801
then I guess
you have your answer, right?

37:26.868 --> 37:31.410
- If an LDS man chooses
to take up polygamy again,

37:31.477 --> 37:34.717
then why not blood atonement?

37:37.088 --> 37:39.359
Slippery slope, isn't it?

37:54.323 --> 37:57.095
Dan Lafferty
is off the ballot for sheriff

37:57.162 --> 38:00.703
for refusing to pay
a $15 processing fee,

38:00.770 --> 38:02.272
but he emerged from jail today

38:02.339 --> 38:05.679
to find he's not off the minds
of local Libertarians.

38:05.746 --> 38:10.589
- He doesn't look too cheesed
off about his failed campaign.

38:10.656 --> 38:12.694
What are we missing here, Jeb?

38:12.760 --> 38:14.931
Motive.

38:14.998 --> 38:16.466
- You all right?

38:16.534 --> 38:18.470
We're chasing our tails.

38:21.544 --> 38:23.915
- What is Robert Wagner
doing here?

38:23.982 --> 38:25.819
- What?
And why are our guys

38:25.886 --> 38:27.890
greeting him like
he's Danny freakin' White?

38:29.426 --> 38:31.029
- I'll take care of it.

38:34.504 --> 38:36.841
- Brother Pyre.

38:36.908 --> 38:40.381
I'm Orton Ballard,
president of Robin's stake.

38:40.448 --> 38:41.785
He phoned me a brief while ago.

38:41.852 --> 38:44.322
- President Ballard,
it's a pleasure to meet you.

38:44.389 --> 38:45.592
How, um, how can I help?

38:45.659 --> 38:49.199
- Well, Robin told me
he's badly in need

38:49.266 --> 38:51.939
of spiritual counsel,
and under the circumstances,

38:52.005 --> 38:54.777
he must be carrying
a heavy burden indeed.

38:54.844 --> 38:55.947
- If--if you're here
to visit him,

38:56.013 --> 39:00.556
I--I ask if it can
wait for tomorrow.

39:00.622 --> 39:03.427
We're--we--the case
is very active right now.

39:03.495 --> 39:07.402
- I know Heavenly Father
won't let you rest

39:07.469 --> 39:09.239
until the evildoers
are in hand,

39:09.306 --> 39:13.782
but Robin's a good boy,
as are Allen and Sam,

39:13.849 --> 39:18.490
and seeing all three
in need of healing prayer,

39:18.558 --> 39:21.531
I'd like you to release them
into my custody.

39:21.598 --> 39:23.034
- Perhaps we can talk
in private.

39:23.100 --> 39:25.906
- Oh, there's no need
to trouble yourself.

39:27.643 --> 39:30.649
- I don't feel it's prudent
to release them just yet.

39:30.716 --> 39:32.419
- Is everything all right?

39:32.485 --> 39:34.958
- It's a very ghastly,
complicated case,

39:35.024 --> 39:36.260
and we're all
doing our best here--

39:36.327 --> 39:39.801
- Oh, no, I mean with you.

39:39.867 --> 39:43.509
You're carrying so much here
and at home--

39:43.575 --> 39:47.482
your mother, her suffering.

39:47.549 --> 39:50.923
Your bishop told me
after he met with you

39:50.990 --> 39:53.495
and your wife
about your daughters' baptism,

39:53.561 --> 39:58.404
you introduced
some provocative questions.

39:58.471 --> 40:00.743
"Blood atonement?"

40:00.810 --> 40:04.049
This case
must weigh heavy on you.

40:04.115 --> 40:07.990
But perhaps some questions
man isn't meant to answer.

40:11.163 --> 40:13.869
Trust the priesthood.

40:13.936 --> 40:16.340
Release the brothers
into my custody.

40:16.407 --> 40:19.179
- Put my questions
on the shelf?

40:21.751 --> 40:23.988
Respectfully, sir,
I'm--I'm not detaining

40:24.055 --> 40:26.561
the Lafferty brothers
for a questioning mind.

40:26.627 --> 40:30.368
I'm investigating a murder.

40:30.435 --> 40:34.611
- We've all made covenants
to protect the Lord's Kingdom,

40:34.678 --> 40:38.384
even unto laying down
our lives.

40:38.451 --> 40:41.525
Now, we wouldn't want anything
to embarrass the church,

40:41.592 --> 40:45.064
would we, Brother?

40:45.131 --> 40:49.206
I trust you recall
the repercussions of sharing

40:49.273 --> 40:51.678
what is heaven's alone.

40:58.090 --> 40:59.593
- Thank you so much.

41:29.787 --> 41:30.889
- Sorry, sir.

41:32.960 --> 41:34.395
What is it?

41:34.462 --> 41:36.100
- Couple boys showed up
at Bishop Low's home,

41:36.167 --> 41:38.070
say they know something
about who broke in.

41:40.475 --> 41:43.515
- All right, good.
Good. Let's go.

41:50.496 --> 41:51.832
So you were rolling around
and you stopped, where?

41:51.899 --> 41:52.800
Right around here, yeah.

41:52.866 --> 41:54.637
- Why'd you stop here?

41:54.704 --> 41:56.473
- The car in the driveway,
it wasn't the Lows',

41:56.541 --> 41:58.077
and there were two men
in the back.

41:58.144 --> 41:59.880
- Did you get a look
at the men?

41:59.947 --> 42:03.154
- Honestly, sir,
we didn't get very close.

42:03.220 --> 42:04.356
They--they worried us.

42:04.423 --> 42:06.594
Why'd they worry you?

42:06.661 --> 42:07.896
- They were just sitting there.

42:07.963 --> 42:09.433
They weren't talking
to each other or anything,

42:09.500 --> 42:11.872
and they had long hair, sir.

42:11.938 --> 42:13.675
- Long like when you need
a haircut or--

42:13.742 --> 42:15.713
- Yes, sir.
Long like a woman's.

42:15.780 --> 42:16.848
All right, good.

42:16.915 --> 42:18.417
- Did you get a look
at the car?

42:18.484 --> 42:20.956
- It was a green station wagon.

42:21.023 --> 42:22.726
An Impala, sir.

42:22.793 --> 42:24.831
My parents had one
until Heavenly Father

42:24.898 --> 42:27.002
answered my prayer
for a Skyhawk.

42:28.939 --> 42:31.511
Green station wagon Impala.
- Yes, sir.

43:07.783 --> 43:09.920
Allen.

43:13.126 --> 43:15.297
This is Ron's car, isn't it?

43:17.503 --> 43:18.771
- Yeah.

43:18.838 --> 43:20.175
- It was spotted at the home
of the Lows'

43:20.241 --> 43:21.712
on the day of the murder.

43:21.778 --> 43:23.782
Now the Lows are missing.

43:23.849 --> 43:26.086
- What are you--
what are you saying?

43:26.153 --> 43:29.627
What, that they got
to Ron, too, or--

43:29.693 --> 43:32.399
or that they stole it?

43:32.466 --> 43:34.469
Or Dan did?

43:34.537 --> 43:37.242
- Dianna sent this.

43:37.308 --> 43:38.945
To the Prophet.

43:41.852 --> 43:44.055
"Dear President Kimball,

43:44.122 --> 43:48.063
"We write aware of how busy
Heavenly Father keeps you.

43:48.898 --> 43:51.003
We need your guidance..."

43:51.070 --> 43:54.042
"So desperately.

43:54.109 --> 43:57.850
"Our husbands have begun
questioning some federal laws

43:57.916 --> 44:01.223
"they believe conflict
with LDS teachings.

44:01.290 --> 44:03.360
"Still, our prayers
tell us that

44:03.427 --> 44:05.165
"a good Mormon abides the law.

44:05.231 --> 44:07.903
"Please counsel us
on Heavenly Father's will.

44:07.970 --> 44:11.043
"Is it ever right
for a Mormon to break a law

44:11.110 --> 44:13.548
"they feel violates
our church beliefs?

44:13.615 --> 44:16.721
My husband--"
Are we sure about this?

44:16.787 --> 44:20.629
- I think so.
I think it's really good.

44:20.695 --> 44:23.467
Yeah?

44:23.534 --> 44:24.604
Yeah!

44:28.512 --> 44:33.621
- Br--Brenda wrote this.

44:33.688 --> 44:35.324
I--I can hear her voice.

44:35.391 --> 44:37.863
Did she ever tell you
about this letter?

44:39.967 --> 44:42.907
No.
At some point, she--

44:42.973 --> 44:47.115
she stopped complaining
about my brothers.

44:47.182 --> 44:50.321
I assumed she...

44:50.387 --> 44:53.260
she'd just
thrown up her hands about them.

44:53.327 --> 44:55.130
And about me.

44:55.197 --> 44:57.603
But, uh,

44:57.670 --> 45:01.511
she still loved me.

45:08.825 --> 45:14.169
She--she'd see, you know, how--

45:14.235 --> 45:17.943
how I struggled
to stand up to them.

45:18.010 --> 45:22.118
So she did the standing.

45:23.955 --> 45:27.797
- Did Ron ever tell you
about this letter?

45:27.863 --> 45:30.234
- No.

45:35.679 --> 45:38.317
- Holy wow, Robin.

45:38.384 --> 45:41.825
You called your stake president
to get you out of jail?

45:41.891 --> 45:44.462
May be the most saintly act
of entitlement

45:44.530 --> 45:46.333
I've ever witnessed.

45:46.400 --> 45:47.803
- You know,
you should really, um,

45:47.869 --> 45:49.439
tell your partner here
who we regard

45:49.506 --> 45:51.878
as the higher authority,
the church or the police.

45:51.945 --> 45:55.351
I don't have to tell you that
disrespecting church authority

45:55.418 --> 45:58.892
puts your own salvation
in the balance.

45:58.958 --> 46:01.196
- Well, there's that.

46:03.200 --> 46:06.072
- If you can answer me
one more question, Robin.

46:06.139 --> 46:10.649
Was Ron at war
with Dan's views...

46:10.715 --> 46:13.354
or was he drawn
to his ideas too?

46:13.420 --> 46:17.094
- Well, Ron stayed out of it
until our father,

46:17.161 --> 46:20.401
who was getting sicker
and weaker,

46:20.468 --> 46:22.773
finally swallowed his pride,
practically begged Ron

46:22.840 --> 46:26.548
to help bring Dan back in line.

46:26.614 --> 46:31.256
- You got to remember
Article of Faith 12.

46:33.694 --> 46:37.736
"We believe in being subject
to kings, presidents, rulers,

46:37.803 --> 46:42.378
"and magistrates
in obeying, honoring,

46:42.445 --> 46:44.517
and sustaining the law."

46:44.583 --> 46:45.885
If you get yourself
thrown in jail,

46:45.952 --> 46:49.225
you're mocking our prophet.
So...

46:49.292 --> 46:53.034
What brought this to mind, Ron?

46:53.100 --> 46:55.271
This unexpected visit?

46:55.338 --> 46:56.942
- I felt a calling
from the Lord.

46:57.008 --> 46:58.444
Oh.

46:58.512 --> 46:59.980
You sure it wasn't
a calling from Dad?

47:01.584 --> 47:04.890
D&C 98, 6 and 7--
"I the Lord justify

47:04.957 --> 47:08.531
"you and your brethren of my
church to befriend the law,

47:08.598 --> 47:10.536
"which is the constitutional
law of the land,

47:10.602 --> 47:14.944
whatsoever is more or less
than this cometh of evil."

47:15.011 --> 47:17.482
And the 16th Amendment
is clearly "more than"

47:17.550 --> 47:19.085
what the Constitution once was.
It is evil.

47:19.152 --> 47:20.889
- Until the--until the church

47:20.956 --> 47:22.559
calls us
to break the law, then--

47:22.626 --> 47:25.331
- It can't.
That is why Joseph wanted us

47:25.398 --> 47:27.770
to directly correspond
with Heavenly Father,

47:27.836 --> 47:30.341
so we should "depend upon
no person for borrowed light,

47:30.407 --> 47:31.878
"trusting only
unto the Holy Spirit,

47:31.944 --> 47:33.047
who is ever the same."

47:33.114 --> 47:34.182
- There's no place
in the church

47:34.248 --> 47:36.053
for extremes, Dan, right?

47:36.120 --> 47:38.558
- What about extremely good,
Ron?

47:38.624 --> 47:39.927
How about extremely good?

47:39.993 --> 47:42.732
The government keeps
changing their rules.

47:42.799 --> 47:46.173
We're simply trying to sustain
the rules that we started with,

47:46.239 --> 47:48.911
our heavenly inspired
constitution.

47:48.978 --> 47:51.584
I mean, it's the only way
out of this mess

47:51.651 --> 47:53.053
and back to God's plan.

47:53.120 --> 47:55.625
- God's plan? What's your plan?
Just to get us thrown in jail?

47:55.692 --> 47:57.228
Is that your plan?
Or are you gonna become sheriff

47:57.294 --> 47:58.965
and stack the juries
and rule how you wish?

47:59.032 --> 48:00.100
Because if you do,
that's an embarrassment.

48:00.167 --> 48:02.438
- Ron.
How do you think we feel?

48:02.505 --> 48:05.512
I--I'm embarrassed I can
barely support my family.

48:05.578 --> 48:07.549
I wish that we could
all be as successful,

48:07.616 --> 48:09.218
as--as well off as you are,
but that's--

48:09.285 --> 48:11.524
Watch your tone with me,
all right?

48:11.591 --> 48:14.429
- I'm sorry.
All right. I'm sorry.

48:14.497 --> 48:16.033
- I'm curious.

48:16.099 --> 48:19.674
Does it help your profits

48:19.740 --> 48:22.045
to obey these illegal laws?

48:22.112 --> 48:24.215
- What?
- Yes or no?

48:27.990 --> 48:30.194
But you follow them anyhow.

48:30.261 --> 48:33.935
And why? Because you're scared.

48:34.002 --> 48:36.039
- Dan--
Dad--Dad'll be gone soon,

48:36.106 --> 48:38.310
and what has he left us with?

48:38.377 --> 48:41.551
Lafferty men used to run things
in this state.

48:41.618 --> 48:44.523
And I've had a vision to set
things back in that order.

48:44.590 --> 48:46.393
Now, if you don't want
to be a part of that,

48:46.460 --> 48:47.361
then you should
change your name

48:47.428 --> 48:49.867
if all we do is embarrass you

48:49.933 --> 48:54.208
because you're either a part
of this family or you are not.

48:59.620 --> 49:01.891
I think it might be time
for you to leave, Ron.

49:01.957 --> 49:04.664
- Okay.
Shut up and let me think.

49:04.731 --> 49:06.534
You know, just--

49:11.276 --> 49:13.982
I do own my own home,
and I do own my own business.

49:14.049 --> 49:15.518
You all know that.

49:15.585 --> 49:19.092
So did someone tell you that
I'm--I'm gonna lose it all?

49:19.159 --> 49:20.261
Is that why you're speaking
this way to me?

49:20.328 --> 49:21.897
- Ron--

49:21.964 --> 49:24.035
You want to cut me down
in front of my own brothers?

49:24.102 --> 49:25.905
Is that what you want?
- Ron.

49:25.972 --> 49:27.441
I did not know that.

49:27.509 --> 49:29.346
- Just--
- Hey, Ron. No, no, no.

49:29.412 --> 49:31.717
- Don't touch me, man.
You shame me.

49:31.784 --> 49:33.220
I didn't know that.

49:36.760 --> 49:39.432
Ron, you suffer
because you're persecuted.

49:39.499 --> 49:42.238
And "persecution has rolled
on our heads from time to time

49:42.305 --> 49:46.045
like peals of thunder
because of our religion."

49:46.112 --> 49:48.851
"Because of our religion," Ron.

49:48.918 --> 49:53.327
So "arise and awaken

49:53.393 --> 49:56.132
unto your awful situation."

49:56.199 --> 49:59.439
They changed the rules on us.

49:59.506 --> 50:01.777
We're gonna put things
back in order.

50:04.148 --> 50:06.452
Robin, will you come help me
hold our brother?

50:09.125 --> 50:10.495
Was this before or after

50:10.561 --> 50:13.133
your dad confronted Dan
at the parade?

50:13.199 --> 50:14.168
It was before.

50:14.235 --> 50:16.306
He only stepped in because

50:16.373 --> 50:18.344
Ron hadn't succeeded with Dan

50:18.410 --> 50:21.917
in the way
that our father had hoped.

50:21.984 --> 50:24.221
- See, Allen claims that--

50:24.288 --> 50:26.694
that Ron had nothing to do
with Dan's ideas.

50:28.864 --> 50:32.105
But now you're telling me...

50:32.171 --> 50:35.210
that Ron followed all of you
until the end?

50:35.277 --> 50:38.718
- I didn't follow Dan
to the end.

50:40.020 --> 50:43.393
But yes,
Dan shifted Ron's mind.

50:43.460 --> 50:46.600
- Did Ron come to Dan's side
before or after this date?

50:47.869 --> 50:49.573
- Before. Well before.

50:49.640 --> 50:51.611
Ron was already with us
when Dianna sent that.

51:00.562 --> 51:02.131
If Robin is telling the truth,

51:02.198 --> 51:04.836
that letter was all about
fixing Ron.

51:04.903 --> 51:06.473
First, Dan brought Ron

51:06.541 --> 51:08.344
into alignment
with his political views.

51:08.410 --> 51:11.049
- So arise and awaken.

51:11.116 --> 51:12.519
- Then Dianna sent the letter.

51:12.585 --> 51:14.557
Yeah?
- Ron.

51:14.623 --> 51:17.428
Then Ron was denied the loan.

51:17.496 --> 51:20.467
And when their father
derailed Dan,

51:20.535 --> 51:22.404
Ron had to take over
Dan's efforts...

51:22.471 --> 51:24.275
- Arise and awake...
Ron, Ron.

51:24.342 --> 51:26.479
- To your awful situation.

51:26.547 --> 51:28.149
His father and his own wife

51:28.216 --> 51:30.588
standing squarely in Ron's way.

51:30.655 --> 51:32.893
See what Bascom says.
- Yeah. You ready?

51:32.960 --> 51:34.931
What line?
- Three.

51:37.201 --> 51:38.370
Ringing.

51:40.407 --> 51:42.078
Good afternoon!
LeConte Bascom.

51:42.144 --> 51:44.082
- Mr. Bascom,
this is Brother Pyre.

51:44.148 --> 51:46.486
Uh, we talked this morning.

51:46.554 --> 51:47.856
Oh, hi.

51:47.923 --> 51:49.292
Detective, how's your day?

51:49.358 --> 51:52.098
To be honest with you,
I--I've lost time

51:52.165 --> 51:53.902
because, uh,

51:53.969 --> 51:56.774
well, see, I worry
you may have fudged the truth

51:56.841 --> 51:59.680
with me this morning about
Ron's reaction to that letter.

51:59.747 --> 52:02.586
- Oh, dear. Uh...

52:02.653 --> 52:04.757
I remembered as best I could,
Brother Pyre.

52:04.823 --> 52:10.568
- Well, see, I don't think
Ron was upset with Dan one bit.

52:12.640 --> 52:15.377
Did you misremember that or did
the Prophet's office set limits

52:15.444 --> 52:17.448
on what you can say?

52:17.516 --> 52:18.885
'Cause they'd rather us
think of Ron

52:18.951 --> 52:23.059
as some kind of saintly victim
of Dan's extracurriculars

52:23.126 --> 52:25.832
because the last thing
they need

52:25.898 --> 52:29.673
is for Utah to find out its
treasured son had gone fundie.

52:29.740 --> 52:33.648
- In all honesty, uh,
anything I might know,

52:33.714 --> 52:35.986
I entrusted to the authority
of Bishop Low.

52:36.052 --> 52:38.658
I'm only in this bishopric.
Maybe speak with him.

52:38.725 --> 52:41.063
In all honesty,
Mr. Bascom,

52:41.129 --> 52:42.666
we can't find the dang Lows.

52:42.732 --> 52:44.636
- I'm sorry, who's this?
Bill Taba.

52:44.703 --> 52:46.807
Detective.
We haven't met yet.

52:46.874 --> 52:49.647
But we can because
if you don't tell us

52:49.713 --> 52:51.817
what you
"entrusted to Bishop Low,"

52:51.884 --> 52:55.157
then I'll cuff your ass and
bring you in for interrogation.

52:55.223 --> 52:58.998
- Uh, uh, forgive me,
I didn't, um,

52:59.064 --> 53:01.771
realize the pertinence
of what I saw until now.

53:01.837 --> 53:05.545
Now, don't you lay the blame
on her feet, all right?

53:05.612 --> 53:07.181
Ron.

53:07.247 --> 53:08.885
Thank you.

53:13.695 --> 53:15.163
- He was upset when I told him

53:15.230 --> 53:16.633
about the letter
his wife wrote.

53:26.587 --> 53:28.123
Shut your--

53:28.190 --> 53:30.996
But I--

53:31.063 --> 53:34.770
I honestly thought it was
just a domestic, Brother Pyre.

53:49.465 --> 53:51.002
- Thank you so much.
Keep me posted.

53:51.069 --> 53:52.471
The Herald and Tribune
are sending reporters.

53:52.539 --> 53:53.841
You want the national outlets?

53:53.908 --> 53:56.045
- No. We just want useful tips,
not publicity.

53:56.112 --> 53:59.185
Yeah, we got an older
model Impala station wagon,

53:59.252 --> 54:00.689
light green.

54:00.755 --> 54:01.990
Hit pause on calling more press

54:02.057 --> 54:03.427
until we fill in the boss.

54:03.494 --> 54:05.966
- Fred, do you mind holding?

54:06.032 --> 54:08.436
Chief. Welcome back.
Thanks for coming back early.

54:08.504 --> 54:10.307
Yeah.
Where are we with suspects?

54:10.374 --> 54:13.379
- We have a station wagon IDed
at a house

54:13.446 --> 54:16.319
targeted by the killers,
belongs to Ron Lafferty.

54:16.385 --> 54:17.622
- Dan Lafferty made contact

54:17.689 --> 54:20.194
with a fundamentalist sect
down south.

54:20.260 --> 54:22.833
We're putting out an APB now.
Absolutely not.

54:22.899 --> 54:24.402
Unless you're ordering pizza,
sunshine,

54:24.469 --> 54:25.939
hang up the phone.

54:26.005 --> 54:27.943
Come on. In my office.

54:28.009 --> 54:30.549
- Welcome back, Chief.

54:30.615 --> 54:32.719
- Time is of the essence.

54:32.786 --> 54:36.894
We--we can enlist the public's
help with a press conference.

54:36.961 --> 54:39.465
All right,
you two know as well as I do.

54:39.532 --> 54:41.203
Outsiders do not understand
the difference

54:41.269 --> 54:44.743
between our church and
the fundies, the polygamists.

54:44.810 --> 54:47.048
We struggle against that
perception every single day.

54:49.151 --> 54:51.389
This is my press conference.

54:51.456 --> 54:53.727
And you two will do as I say.

54:55.130 --> 54:57.368
And of course, a big thank you

54:57.435 --> 55:00.709
to our detectives,
Jeb Pyre, Bill Taba.

55:00.775 --> 55:02.879
They have been delivering
solid investigative work

55:02.946 --> 55:05.785
that is gonna bring
this troubling situation

55:05.852 --> 55:07.088
to a quick close.

55:07.154 --> 55:10.026
Detectives have a quick update
as to where we're at.

55:10.093 --> 55:11.196
Jeb?

55:11.262 --> 55:12.665
Thank you, sir.

55:14.402 --> 55:16.807
Afternoon.

55:16.874 --> 55:17.909
At this point,

55:17.976 --> 55:20.280
we're not able
to name a suspect,

55:20.347 --> 55:22.953
but we are asking the public
to help us locate a vehicle

55:23.019 --> 55:26.492
we think may be connected
to the crime.

55:26.560 --> 55:28.698
It's a green Chevrolet Impala.

55:33.508 --> 55:36.346
A as in Ada, 2-8-3.

55:36.412 --> 55:37.849
Detective,
were the murders ritualistic?

55:37.916 --> 55:39.753
Have you identified a motive?

55:39.820 --> 55:42.057
Are women with
young children being targeted?

55:46.701 --> 55:50.074
- At this point, we don't think
that the public generally

55:50.140 --> 55:52.979
needs to be afraid,
but we are a community

55:53.046 --> 55:55.785
that isn't used
to locking its doors.

55:55.852 --> 55:58.223
For the time being, we should
all err on the side of caution.

55:58.290 --> 55:59.626
Okay? Thank you.

55:59.693 --> 56:01.195
Sir,
do you suspect fundamentalism

56:01.262 --> 56:03.033
as a motive for these murders?

56:03.100 --> 56:07.709
Uh, we, uh, are aware of
a constitutional fundamentalist

56:07.776 --> 56:10.849
anti-tax group's proximity
to these events,

56:10.915 --> 56:12.886
but we've found no direct link.
Thank you.

56:12.953 --> 56:14.723
How about
Mormon fundamentalists?

56:14.790 --> 56:16.258
- That's enough, gentlemen.
Thank you so much.

56:16.325 --> 56:17.763
Thank you. Thank you very much.
- Detective Pyre.

56:17.829 --> 56:19.633
Why were you present
at a cabin raid

56:19.699 --> 56:22.305
outside of your jurisdiction?
Was that raid related?

56:22.371 --> 56:28.016
And if so, which is it?
Satanists, FLDS, or neither?

56:34.963 --> 56:36.700
It's quite a simple question.

56:46.019 --> 56:48.023
- Personally,

56:48.089 --> 56:51.195
I wouldn't rule out
fundamentalist Mormonism.

56:51.262 --> 56:52.833
Why? What have you found?

56:52.900 --> 56:54.335
Thank you, gentlemen.
That's enough.

56:54.402 --> 56:55.871
No, detective,
what have you seen--

57:12.071 --> 57:14.610
- Hey. You should, uh...

57:14.676 --> 57:15.778
- Yeah, let's get up
to Granddaddy Mountain

57:15.845 --> 57:17.214
and find Morris.
I'm ready.

57:17.281 --> 57:20.453
- I was gonna say you should
take the night off.

57:22.257 --> 57:23.827
Forgive my language...

57:26.232 --> 57:28.469
But I'm goddamn proud of you.

57:31.309 --> 57:32.912
You did the right thing.

57:34.883 --> 57:37.321
So go, get some sleep.

57:37.387 --> 57:39.091
You may well need it.

57:39.158 --> 57:40.861
- Thanks, pal.

58:19.171 --> 58:20.642
- Oh, no.

58:32.632 --> 58:35.236
I'm looking for Fern Lake.

58:37.207 --> 58:39.245
- You're lost.

58:39.312 --> 58:41.349
- Hey, hey.

59:01.489 --> 59:03.126
- Brother.

59:12.444 --> 59:14.047
- Aren't we blessed?

59:14.114 --> 59:16.620
- Good morning, Sister Dorren.
Yes, of course.

59:16.686 --> 59:19.425
- Um, my husband and I
have been praying

59:19.491 --> 59:21.964
with Stake President Ballard

59:22.030 --> 59:25.137
to see you through
your current confusion.

59:30.447 --> 59:32.552
- To conceive three children
that you will not meet

59:32.618 --> 59:35.724
till you get to heaven

59:35.791 --> 59:38.564
is a heavy burden, Sister.

59:38.631 --> 59:41.971
But they are waiting
for you in heaven.

59:42.037 --> 59:44.107
And we cannot let them down.

59:46.713 --> 59:49.652
He's given you
these two beautiful girls.

59:51.557 --> 59:55.698
Sometimes, when we wait
a long time for something,

59:55.765 --> 59:57.836
it's hard to accept
when it's finally here.

59:57.902 --> 59:59.839
But it is here.

1:00:02.277 --> 1:00:05.350
Your children have reached
the age of accountability,

1:00:05.417 --> 1:00:08.991
and it is time for your girls

1:00:09.057 --> 1:00:12.899
to be baptized
into His one true church.

1:00:16.640 --> 1:00:17.708
- We should head in.
Thank you.

1:00:17.775 --> 1:00:19.344
Thank you.
Bless you. Yes.

1:00:21.015 --> 1:00:22.685
Where are you taking me?

1:00:29.999 --> 1:00:33.206
Hello?

1:00:33.273 --> 1:00:35.244
Mister?

1:00:40.555 --> 1:00:42.224
Dear Heavenly Father...

1:00:43.928 --> 1:00:45.463
With your blessing--

1:01:04.536 --> 1:01:06.238
Bishop Low!

1:01:09.679 --> 1:01:11.315
Thank--thank you!

1:01:12.786 --> 1:01:14.355
Bishop Low!
